{% extends "base.html.twig" %}

{% block title %}Technology — Your Nation's platform, owned not rented · FNPI{% endblock %}
{% block description %}Anokii is the sovereign workspace for First Nations: website, member portal, drive, and AI in one system the Nation owns, hosted in Canada, governed by Council.{% endblock %}

{% block head_styles %}
  .modgrid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:14px}
  .mod{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:4px;padding:18px 18px 20px}
  .mod h4{margin:0 0 6px;font-size:16px;color:var(--ink)}
  .mod p{margin:0;font-size:13.5px;color:var(--muted)}
  .mod .tag{font-family:"Oswald",sans-serif;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.1em;color:#7a4e1d;background:#f3e9da;border-radius:2px;padding:2px 7px;display:inline-block;margin-bottom:8px}
  .checks{list-style:none;margin:0;padding:0;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:12px 28px}
  .checks li{padding-left:26px;position:relative;color:var(--muted)}
  .checks li b{color:var(--ink)}
  .checks li::before{content:"";position:absolute;left:0;top:7px;width:12px;height:12px;border:2px solid var(--cyan);border-radius:2px}
  @media(max-width:880px){.modgrid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}.checks{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<section class="hero">
  <div class="grid-bg"></div><div class="glow"></div>
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">Sovereign technology for Nations</p>
    <h1 class="display">Your Nation's platform.<br>Owned, not rented.</h1>
    <p class="oneline">One connected system the Nation owns, hosted in Canada, governed by Council, with AI built in.</p>
    <div class="cta">
      <a class="btn cyan" href="/contact">Request a quote</a>
      <a class="btn ghost" href="/how-it-works">See how it works</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section><div class="wrap">
  <p class="sec-h">The problem: own vs rent</p>
  <h2 class="sec-t display">The money is already leaving the community.</h2>
  <p class="sec-sub" style="margin-left:0">Most Nations run on tools they do not own: commercial Microsoft 365 seats billed every year, data sitting in a US-reachable cloud under the CLOUD Act, a website nobody can edit, and the real work scattered across disconnected spreadsheets. You pay forever and own nothing. We redirect that same spend into a stack the Nation owns, and add what the rented tools never gave you.</p>
</div></section>

<section class="band"><div class="wrap">
  <p class="sec-h">Anokii, the sovereign workspace</p>
  <h2 class="display">One system. One login. One record across departments.</h2>
  <p class="sec-sub" style="margin-left:0">Anokii is built on the Waaseyaa engine: an entity-first, AI-native platform. Instead of a dozen rented apps that do not talk to each other, the Nation runs on one workspace it controls.</p>
  <div class="modgrid">
    <div class="mod"><h4>Website</h4><p>A fast, branded public site with a real editable backend.</p></div>
    <div class="mod"><h4>Member Portal</h4><p>Secure services and information for members, online.</p></div>
    <div class="mod"><h4>Drive</h4><p>The Nation's files and documents, stored in Canada.</p></div>
    <div class="mod"><h4>Co-Intelligence</h4><p>A built-in AI assistant grounded on your own files.</p></div>
    <div class="mod"><h4>Data Rooms</h4><p>Controlled spaces for sensitive negotiations and records.</p></div>
    <div class="mod"><h4>Workspaces</h4><p>Department workspaces that share one source of truth.</p></div>
    <div class="mod"><h4>Governance</h4><p>Council records, motions, and decisions in one place.</p></div>
    <div class="mod"><h4>Vault</h4><p>Encrypted storage for the records that matter most.</p></div>
  </div>
</div></section>

<section class="faraday"><div class="wrap"><div class="grid">
  <div>
    <p class="sec-h" style="color:#7fd6e8">AI is core, not an add-on</p>
    <h2 class="sec-t display">Co-Intelligence</h2>
    <p class="sec-sub">Anokii's assistant is grounded on the Nation's own files, so answers come from your records, not the open internet. Meeting-minutes transcription runs locally, so the audio and the minutes stay in Canada. The AI is part of the platform from day one, helping a small office do the work of a much larger one.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="panel"><div class="g"></div><span>Grounded on your files</span></div>
</div></div></section>

<section class="center"><div class="wrap">
  <p class="sec-h">Sovereignty, concretely</p>
  <h2 class="sec-t display">This is the answer to CLOUD Act exposure.</h2>
  <p class="sec-sub">Sovereignty is not a slogan here. It is how the platform is built.</p>
  <ul class="checks" style="text-align:left">
    <li><b>Canadian incorporation and data residency.</b> Your data lives in Canada, under Canadian law.</li>
    <li><b>Per-Nation isolation.</b> Each Nation's data is its own; never pooled, never resold.</li>
    <li><b>Member access and export rights.</b> The Nation can get its data out, any time.</li>
    <li><b>OCAP alignment.</b> Ownership, Control, Access, and Possession stay with the Nation.</li>
  </ul>
</div></section>

<section class="band"><div class="wrap">
  <p class="sec-h">Department modules</p>
  <h2 class="display">What you can grow into.</h2>
  <p class="sec-sub" style="margin-left:0"><b>Roadmap, added one at a time, each owned by the Nation.</b> The platform and the first modules are what we are building now; the rest below is the roadmap you grow into as trust builds, not a suite that all ships today.</p>
  <ul class="checks" style="text-align:left">
    <li>Housing and assets</li>
    <li>Income assistance</li>
    <li>Finance and ISC reporting</li>
    <li>Membership and registry</li>
    <li>Governance and BCRs</li>
    <li>Health intake / Jordan's Principle</li>
    <li>Lands</li>
    <li>Emergency management</li>
    <li>HR and payroll with Section 87</li>
  </ul>
</div></section>

<section class="center"><div class="wrap">
  <p class="sec-h">Hosted in Canada</p>
  <h2 class="sec-t display">Sovereign software, on a path to sovereign infrastructure.</h2>
  <p class="sec-sub">Today the platform is hosted on Web Networks, a Canadian, Indigenous-aligned provider. The long-term goal is First Nations-owned hosting, so the infrastructure becomes as sovereign as the software running on it.</p>
</div></section>

<section class="hero"><div class="grid-bg"></div><div class="wrap" style="text-align:center;padding:64px 26px">
  <h2 class="display" style="font-size:44px;color:#fff;margin:0 0 22px">Own your Nation's platform.</h2>
  <div class="cta" style="justify-content:center">
    <a class="btn cyan" href="/contact">Request a quote</a>
    <a class="btn ghost" href="/how-it-works">See how it works</a>
  </div>
</div></section>
{% endblock %}
